Title
Stress test inline naming duplication under worst-case path and fragmentation scenarios

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Evaluate whether the inline naming design introduced in FORMAT-12 (`extent_identity_inline_path`) causes unacceptable archive size growth under extreme path duplication and fragmentation conditions.

This packet verifies that the FORMAT-12 design remains compression-credible under adversarial datasets.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

Context

FORMAT-12 demonstrated that embedding path/name information into each extent identity record restored full named recovery while adding only ~4.7% archive overhead.

However, the test corpus did not strongly stress the duplication risk created by repeating paths in each extent identity record.

Worst-case scenarios include:

- extremely long paths
- deeply nested directory structures
- heavily fragmented files
- many small extents per file

This packet measures whether those conditions cause archive size explosion.

